1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:11,810
Because you got up at 5.30 a.m. to deliver papers or milk the cows when you were a youngster doesn't necessarily mean it's a good idea for you to require your children to do the same.

2
00:00:13,040 --> 00:00:18,770
Imagine what would happen to the Ford Motor Company if its management allowed itself to think,

3
00:00:19,040 --> 00:00:22,209
this year we've built the ultimate in automobiles.

4
00:00:22,240 --> 00:00:24,449
Further improvement is impossible.

5
00:00:24,640 --> 00:00:31,490
Therefore, all experimental engineering and designing activities are hereby permanently terminated.

6
00:00:31,840 --> 00:00:36,770
Even the mammoth Ford Motor Company would shrivel fast with this attitude.

7
00:00:37,360 --> 00:00:42,130
Successful people, like successful businesses, live with these questions.

8
00:00:42,320 --> 00:00:45,490
How can I improve the quality of my performance?

9
00:00:45,680 --> 00:00:47,170
How can I do better?

10
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:55,250
Absolute perfection in all human undertakings, from building missiles to rearing children, is unattainable.

11
00:00:55,440 --> 00:00:58,530
This means there is endless room for improvement.

12
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:03,490
Successful people know this, and they are always searching for a better way.

13
00:01:03,760 --> 00:01:08,130
Note, the successful person doesn't ask, can I do it better?

14
00:01:08,320 --> 00:01:09,650
He knows he can.

15
00:01:09,840 --> 00:01:13,810
So he phrases the question, how can I do it better?

